column1: #Text=The town lies at the crossroads of the Fosse Way ( the ancient Roman road ) and the A44 and next to the River Evenlode ( a tributary of the River Thames ) .
#Text=The town and nearby countryside are low lying and flat given how the town is considered to be in " Cotswold Hills Country " .

column1: #Text=The " Moreton " from the town name means " Farmstead on the Moor " .
#Text=The town 's architecture is typical of the area , buildings being constructed of local cotswold stone .
#Text=The town lies on the A44 east-west main road running between Oxford and Aberystwyth , passing through Chipping Norton to the E and through Evesham to the W.
#Text=The town lie son the A429 main road running between the M4 motorway ( near Chippenham ) to Coventry to the north .
#Text=Great Western trains from London Paddington via Oxford , Hereford via Great Malvern and Worcester .
#Text=Pulham Coaches Service 801 runs Moreton-in-Marsh – Stow-on-the-Wold – Bourton-on-the-Water – Northleach – Andoversford – Cheltenham
#Text=Pulham Coaches Service 801 runs Bourton-on-the-Water – Upper Oddington – Longborough – Moreton-in-Marsh

#Text=Lincoln to Exeter will run through the town ; the route is under construction , Cirencester - Northleach and Moreton-in-Marsh- Southam completed ( 10-mile section through Bourton-on-the-Water under construction as of 2017 ) .
#Text=The town is small enough to see on foot .
#Text=Batsford Arboretum ( about 1½ miles north-west of Moreton-in-Marsh ) .
#Text=55-acre arboretum and botanical garden containing around 2,900 trees , with a large collection of Japanese maples , magnolias and pines .
#Text=Wellington Aviation Museum , British School House , Broadway Road , GL56 0BG , ☏ +441608650323 .
#Text=Small museum about Second World War RAF Moreton-in-Marsh .
#Text=Maintained by the National Trust since 1991 , when it was acquired from the last representative of the family who had owned the house since it was first built .

#Text=It is one of England ’s finest and most complete Jacobean houses , filled not only with a mixture of rare and everyday objects , furniture and textiles collected since its completion in 1612 , but also with the atmosphere of 400 years of continuous occupation by one family .
#Text=The gardens have a typical Elizabethan and Jacobean layout with a ring of fascinating topiary at their heart and it was here in 1865 that the rules of modern croquet were codified .
#Text=Since acquiring the property , the Trust has concentrated on conserving it rather than restoring it to a pristine state .
#Text=Sezincote House , near Moreton-in-Marsh GL56 9AW ( 3½ mils W of Moreton-in-Marsh ) , ✉ enquiries@sezincote.com .
#Text=House : May-Sep Th F 2:30-5:30PM ; garden : Jan-Nov Th F 2-6PM. House ( including garden ) £10 ; garden only adults £5 , children £1.50 .
#Text=Bourton House Gardens , Bourton on the Hill GL56 9AE ( 2 miles W of Moreton-in-Marsh ) , ☏ +441386700754 , ✉ info@bourtonhouse.com .
#Text=Stone marking the point where the boundaries of Worcestershire , Warwickshire , Oxfordshire and Gloucestershire met .
#Text=In 1931 the county boundaries were " re-organised " and now the store only marks the meeting of Gloucestershire , Warwickshire and Oxfordshire ( though the name was retained ! ) .

#Text=On Tuesday morning , there is a local market on the High Street .
#Text=A great place to pick up some fresh produce or cheap power tools , some doilies or wool sweaters .
